-- Mauritius Sugar Output to Decline in 2012, l’Express Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-06-01T07:30:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-01/mauritius-sugar-output-to-decline-in-2012-l-express-says.html
Mauritius’s sugar production in 2012
will be lower than last year’s 435,000 metric tons, l’Express
reported, without saying where it obtained the information.  Unsuitable climatic conditions and a decline in land area
under cane cultivation are the main reasons cited for the
decline, the Port Louis-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  